“ There you have two dowers of the saith, the gift of the Father supreme, which He has given to the city of the toga to reverence. See, the people of Romulus goes pouring through the streets two separate ways, for the same day is busy with two festivals. But let us hasten with quickened step to both and in each get full enjoyment of the songs of praise. We shall go further on, where the way leads over Hadrian’s bridge‚⁶ and afterwards seek the left bank of the river. The sleepless bishop performs the sacred ceremonies first across the Tiber,⁶ then hurries back to this side and repeats his offeringsst It is enough for you to have learned all this at Rome ; when you return home, remember to keep this day of two festivals as you see it here.''
